VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'description. It\'s from my GitHub repo where I keep all my Colab notebooks. The FlashHead one is at the very top at the moment. Click it, and it opens directly in Colab. First thing, before you do anything else, check your runtime, top'

[06:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'right corner. It needs to say T4 GPU. If it\'s showing CPU, click the drop down, go to change runtime type, select T4, and save. Now, before you hit run all,'

[07:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'let me explain one thing I built into this notebook. The default FlashHead setup as a frustrating limitation. No matter what aspect ratio you give it, the output always comes out as a one-to-one square, totally useless for'

[07:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'YouTube or social content. So, I wrote a patch that detects your input aspect ratio, crops just the face to one-to-one for the generation, then stitches the result back onto your original frame.'

[07:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You put in 16:9, you get 16:9 back. 9:16 in, 9:16 out. The background stays static, which is completely fine since all the movement is in the head anyway. Now, hit run all, and let me walk you'

[07:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'through each cell. Firstly, it connects to the GPU. Watch the top right corner, it\'ll flip from connecting to connected. Once that\'s done, everything runs automatically. Cell one verifies your CUDA setup and available VRAM. Cell two'

[07:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'clones the repo. Cell three installs dependencies. This takes about 2 to 3 minutes, just let it run. Cell four downloads the models from Hugging Face. You\'ll see progress bars for the pro'

[08:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model, light model, Wave2Vec, and the remaining FlashHead components. Wait for all of them to hit 100%. Cell five runs my aspect ratio and Gradio patch. Cell six locks in the face crop behavior. And'

[08:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the final cell launches the Gradio interface. You\'ll get two links. Use the public one, not the local URL. The Gradio UI is minimal and clean. Image on the left, audio on the right, generate button below. There\'s a default'

[08:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sample image and audio already loaded, so you can test immediately. Under advanced settings, the model is set to light by default. Faster, and with the trick I\'ll show you, the quality gets very close to pro. If you want the best'

[08:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quality and you\'re willing to wait, switch to pro from the drop-down. On the inference tab, there\'s a stream versus once toggle. It doesn\'t matter which you pick on a T4, you\'ll only see the output once generation is fully complete either'

[08:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'way. Leave everything else as is. The face crop is already forced on, and the model paths are pre-filled. Let me show you a live generation now. I\'m uploading a 9:16 portrait image of a model. This will also confirm the aspect ratio fix'

